    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180&deg;C/ 160&deg;C (fan)/ 350&deg;F/ Gas 4</p> <p>Boil a kettle</p> <p>Add the <strong>baby plum&nbsp;tomatoes</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> sugar</strong></p> <p>Put them in the oven to slow-roast until serving (approx. 30 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ultimate-mac-and-cheese/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the&nbsp;<strong>conchiglie&nbsp;</strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of<strong>&nbsp;salt</strong>&nbsp;and bring to the boil over a high heat</p> <p>Cook the<strong>&nbsp;conchiglie</strong>&nbsp;for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p> <p>Once done, drain the<strong>&nbsp;conchiglie</strong>, reserving 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> of the&nbsp;<strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ultimate-mac-and-cheese/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the<strong>&nbsp;streaky bacon</strong>&nbsp;into small, bite-size pieces</p> <p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat and once hot, add 2/3 of the <strong>chopped&nbsp;bacon</strong> (save the rest for later!)</p> <p>Cook for 3-4 min or until crisped, then transfer to <strong>kitchen paper</strong> and set aside (keep the pan!)</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ultimate-mac-and-cheese/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel the&nbsp;<strong>garlic</strong></p> <p>Grate the&nbsp;<strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p> <p>Grate the<strong>&nbsp;cheddar&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>Drain, pat dry and rip the&nbsp;<strong>mozzarella&nbsp;</strong>into small, bite-size pieces</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ultimate-mac-and-cheese/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the&nbsp;pan to a medium heat and once hot, add 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span>&nbsp;<strong>butter</strong></p> <p>Once melted, add 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span><strong>&nbsp;flour&nbsp;</strong>and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms - this is your<strong> roux</strong></p> <p>Gradually whisk 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span><strong>&nbsp;milk</strong>&nbsp;into the roux and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains - this is your&nbsp;<strong>b&eacute;chamel sauce&nbsp;</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ultimate-mac-and-cheese/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate the<strong>&nbsp;garlic</strong>&nbsp;into the&nbsp;<strong>b&eacute;chamel sauce</strong>&nbsp;and season with a generous pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>pepper&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>Once thickened, add the<strong>&nbsp;Italian hard cheese</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>cheddar</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>wholegrain mustard</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>crispy bacon</strong> and<strong>&nbsp;drained conchigle</strong>&nbsp;with a few splashes of<strong>&nbsp;starchy pasta water</strong>&nbsp;to loosen the mixture</p> <p>Tip: you want your sauce to be quite loose as it will continue to thicken in the oven!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ultimate-mac-and-cheese/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the <strong>slow roasted tomatoes</strong> from the oven and set them aside until serving</p> <p>Increase the oven temperature to&nbsp;240&deg;C/ 220&deg;C (fan)/ 475&deg;F/ Gas 9</p> <p>Transfer the<strong>&nbsp;cheesy pasta&nbsp;</strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong>, then top with the<strong> ripped mozzarella</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>&nbsp;and the remaining <strong>chopped bacon</strong>, drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and put the dish in the oven for 20-25 min or until it's golden</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ultimate-mac-and-cheese/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper&nbsp;</strong>- this is your<strong>&nbsp;balsamic dressing</strong></p> <p>Gently toss the&nbsp;<strong>baby leaf</strong>&nbsp;<strong>mixed</strong>&nbsp;<strong>salad</strong> with the <strong>slow roasted tomatoes</strong>&nbsp;and drizzle with the <strong>balsamic dressing</strong> when you're ready to serve</p> <p>Enjoy!&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
